Program: Discovery
Title: Spectrum - golden rice
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxmh
Last Broadcast Date: 06 June 2000
Report on the development of gene-altered rice. The rice, known as golden rice, is designed to help increase the vitamin A intake of millions of people. Lack of vitamin A is one of the world's most common deficiency and a leading cause of child mortality. With studio guest Professor Ingo Potrykus.